25 Jesus referred to a </div><div class="t m1ad5 x27 h2b y1d1c ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">division of people. Of those in the field </div><div class="t m7b4 x27 h2b y1aba ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and at the mill &quot;one shall be taken and </div><div class="t m1346 x27 h2b yb45 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the other left.&quot; In the story of the faith-</div><div class="t m18a5 x27 h2b y1d75 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ful and evil servants the first was pro-</div><div class="t m1e60 x27 h2b y1b8e ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">moted, the other punished. Five of the </div><div class="t mf54 x27 h2b y1da8 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bridesmaids went to the wedding and five </div><div class="t mb29 x27 h2b y1595 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">were excluded. In the story of the talents </div><div class="t m156f x27 h2b y1ce6 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the faithful servants were commended and </div><div class="t mae9 x27 h2b y1bb4 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">promoted, the unfaithful servant was re-</div><div class="t m231 x27 h2b y1a99 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">buked, discharged, and punished. In each </div><div class="t m49c x27 h2b y18f0 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">case a judgment is taught but the nature of </div><div class="t m189 x27 h2b y1c4e ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the judgment is not revealed. This parable </div><div class="t m1221 x15 h2b y1a03 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">explains what the judgment is about. </div><div class="t m48b x7d h2e y1a03 ff6 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(3) </div><div class="t ma64 x15 h2b y1e6d ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In the parable of the talents the division </div><div class="t m14c6 x27 h2b y152f ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was on the basis of faithfulness-unfaith-</div><div class="t m2b5 x27 h2b y1abe ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fulness. In last week&apos;s lesson we noted that </div><div class="t m59e x27 h2b y1a2f ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">this faithfulness or unfaithfulness was do-</div><div class="t mad4 x15 h2b y1c99 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ing or not 